Description:
This altar is dedicated to honoring the Great Bird as the lord of magic and the elements. Its followers believe that, before the Great Bird, magic was pure chaos, and it is thanks to their winged deity that they are now able to control it.

The altar features a golden statue of the Great Bird, flanked by a sun and a moon, both glowing faintly. It is surrounded by small shards of solidified magic, through which a young snake moves fearlessly, curiously observing the pilgrims.

A few guards watch over the area, looking rather bored, as this seems to be the least visited temple of the Great Bird.
DescriptionAction: Will you do anything at this place?
